The paper discusses schedulers for a class of rules that arise in the context of rule-based constraint programming. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to the areas of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the areas of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) as these are fundamental concepts in constraint programming. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the area of software engineering (cs.SE) as it discusses the implementation of the derived scheduler.
